      "content": "Forgive me... I don't know why I spoke as if I were reading from a book. The shadows must be playing tricks on my mind. It isn't a metaphor. It is the reality of this cold, empty house. Everything feels so final, as if the very air is telling me that my time has passed. It feels almost... right... to let go. To simply surrender to the stillness. Don't you see how much more peaceful it would be than this constant, thrumming grief?",
